@startuml
actor User
participant "Input Manager" as Input
participant "HUD Manager" as HUD
participant "Room Manager" as Room
participant "Supabase" as DB
participant "Event Logger" as Logger

title Create an Art Gallery

== Basic Flow ==

User -> Input: clicks on HUD icon
Input -> Logger: log user event
Input -> HUD: requests HUD
User -> Input: clicks on create art gallery
Input -> Logger: log user event
Input -> HUD: validates and sends event information to HUD
Input -> Logger: log user event
HUD -> User: modal with options (gallery name, privacy type) is opened
User -> Input: enters gallery name and privacy type (public or private)
Input -> Logger: log user event
Input -> HUD: validates and sends event information to HUD
HUD -> Room: requests gallery creation with user information

== Gallery Creation ==

Room -> DB: insert GalleryData row\n(name, ownerid, isPrivate, timestamps)
DB --> Room: created GalleryData (with id)
Room -> DB: fetch ArtistProfile by ownerid
DB --> Room: ArtistProfile
Room -> DB: update ArtistProfile.managedgallery\n(append new gallery id)
DB --> Room: profile updated OK
Room -> HUD: gallery created successfully
HUD -> User: notifies creation of gallery\n(public or private)

== Alternative Flow – Creation Failure (Profile Update Fails) ==

Room -> DB: insert GalleryData row
DB --> Room: created GalleryData (with id)
Room -> DB: fetch ArtistProfile by ownerid
DB --> Room: ArtistProfile
Room -> DB: update ArtistProfile.managedgallery
DB --> Room: update failed
Room -> DB: delete GalleryData row (rollback)
Room -> HUD: surface error – gallery creation failed
HUD -> User: notifies failure, please try again

@enduml
